* compute `steps_per_epoch` with `train_batch_size`

* flattened semantic_segmentation loss attributes

Add output_stride parameter to quantize.md

The default output_stride in export_model.py is 8. The example in quantize.md is a model that expects an output_stride of 16. So if you try to use export_model.py without setting the output_stride, the resulting model will convert to tflite fine but with the wrong output_stride. This likely produces an invalid model. In my use case where I wanted to compile the model for an edgetpu, I suspect that this issue with the resulting model was causing the compiler to abort.

Fix tfjs export.

There's a `BroadcastArgs` operation in
linear_to_mel_weight_matrix -> linspace that tfjs cannot convert.

So `linear_to_mel_weight_matrix` can't run while the model's
executing. It needs to run before.

A `tf.init_scope` runs with eager execution [1] allowing you to calculate
the constant value outside of the graph that's being built.

I don't see how this could work before my change, unless the
`BroadcastArgs` was added later, or my change prevents somehow prevents
an optimization step from removing the `BroadcastArgs`.

[1] https://www.tensorflow.org/api_docs/python/tf/init_scope

> When eager execution is enabled, code inside an init_scope block runs
with eager execution enabled even when tracing a tf.function.
